│
├── model/
│   └── trained_model.pkl
│
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md

## How to Run the Project

1. Clone the repository
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/loan-eligibility-prediction.git

2. Navigate to the project directory
   cd loan-eligibility-prediction

3. Install required libraries
   pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the Jupyter Notebook
   jupyter notebook

## Results

The Random Forest model achieved the best performance compared to other algorithms. Credit history and income were the most important features influencing loan approval.

## Future Scope

- Deploy the model using Flask or Streamlit
- Improve accuracy using hyperparameter tuning
- Add real-time prediction interface
- Use advanced algorithms like XGBoost.
